The petrol price will decrease by between R0.68 and R0.71 from Wednesday, the mineral resources and energy ministry said on Monday. The following price updates were announced: According to a statement from the ministry, the reductions were based on international and local factors, including  the rand depreciating against the  dollar (from R15.40 to R15.92 per USD) and the decrease in the price of crude oil from $83 to $76 per barrel. TimesLIVE